putDatastream

public FedoraObject putDatastream(Datastream ds)
Adds or replaces a datastream in this object. If a datastream already exists in the object with a matching id, it will be replaced by this one. This is a convenience method which is equivalent to: 
     obj.datastreams().put(ds.id(), ds);

Parameters:
ds - the value to add, never null.
Returns:
this instance.
Throws:
NullPointerException - if the value is null.

datastreams

public SortedMap<String,Datastream> datastreams()
Gets the (mutable) map of datastreams in this object. Iterators over the keys of the map will provide the values in alphabetical order (descending) according to their ids.

The returned map ensures that when datastreams are added via put(key, value), the key matches the id of the datastream. If this is violated, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.

Any attempt to put a null key or value will result in a NullPointerException.

Returns:
the value, possibly empty, never null.
